"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-01-paris-2024-olympics-ajibade-laments-super-falcons-early-exit-thanks-fans\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Rasheedat Ajibade has expressed disappointment with the Super Falcons early ouster from the 2024 Olympic Games.  The Super Falcons exited the women's football event following a 3-1 defeat to Japan on Wednesday.  Randy Waldrum's side lost all three group games, scoring one goal and conceding five.  Ajibade however appreciate the fans for their support despite the team's poor showing.  \\\"It was a disappointing outcome in the end for the team after three tough tests against some of the best football teams in the world,\\\" the Atletico Madrid winger wrote on X.  \\\"We thank you for your endless love and support. We appreciate every one of you. In all, we give thanks to God.\\\"  LaLiga: Iheanacho ready to deliver for Sevilla  Transfer: Chelsea agree deal to sell Lukaku to EPL rivals as Osimhen move stalls  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  NWFL: Delta Queens appoint Ajibade new head coach  Otti hosts Super Falcon players in Abia, says they are role models  Super Falcons aim to become global powerhouse - Ajibade  CAF Awards: Ajibade, Okoronkwo nominated for Women's Player of the Year  Ebi: Ajibade, Ohale celebrates former Super Falcons captain  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"